  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444_3",
    "text": "2.形容词比较级的常用句型",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.09047276217902568,
      0.08888888888888889,
      0.3851691864650828,
      0.10829765545361876
    ],
    "page": "jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444",
    "order": 4
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444_10",
    "text": "",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6779457643388529,
      0.0963914373088685,
      0.960883129349652,
      0.32391437308868504
    ],
    "page": "jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444",
    "order": 5
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444_4",
    "text": "(1)两者比较：“A+be形容词比较级thanB.”表 “A比B.…”,，than是比较级句式的标志词。 Shanghai is smaller than Liuzhou.上海比柳州小。 (2)选择性比较：“Which/Who+be+形容词比较级，A orB?”表示“A与B，哪一个/谁更…?”。 Which is bigger, the sun or the moon? 太阳和月亮哪一个更大？ (3)“A+be+the+形容词比较级+of the two(+复数 名词).”表示“A是两者中比较……的”。 2 He is the taller of the treo boys. 他是两个男孩中比较高的。",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.08567314614830814,
      0.11319062181447502,
      0.6611471082313415,
      0.37398572884811415
    ],
    "page": "jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444",
    "order": 6
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444_11",
    "text": "A. big B. bigger C. biggest",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6805855531557475,
      0.3250560652395515,
      0.9282457403407728,
      0.36664627930682975
    ],
    "page": "jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444",
    "order": 7
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444_12",
    "text": "点拨：可用固定搭配法解答 本题。not as.. as..是同级 比较的句式，意为“不 如…”，中间用形容词原 级。故选A。",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6793856491480682,
      0.37121304791029563,
      0.9577633789296857,
      0.4822833843017329
    ],
    "page": "jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444",
    "order": 8
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444_5",
    "text": "【名师提醒】",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.08663306935445164,
      0.37871559633027524,
      0.21142308615310776,
      0.3977981651376147
    ],
    "page": "jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444",
    "order": 9
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444_6",
    "text": "比较级的前面通常用much(…得多）、alot(……得 多）、alittle(稍微）以及even（甚至)等修饰，从某种意义 上讲，这些也是比较级的标志词。但very和quite不能 修饰比较级。",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.08567314614830814,
      0.40318042813455657,
      0.6570674346052315,
      0.4969622833843017
    ],
    "page": "jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444",
    "order": 10
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444_7",
    "text": "Mrs Huang became much richer after she opened a flower shop. 黄女士开了一家花店后变得富裕多了。",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.08375329973602112,
      0.5020183486238532,
      0.6565874730021598,
      0.5718246687054026
    ],
    "page": "jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444",
    "order": 11
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444_13",
    "text": "助记",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.7139428845692345,
      0.5170234454638124,
      0.7660187185025198,
      0.5349643221202854
    ],
    "page": "jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444",
    "order": 12
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444_14",
    "text": "比较级歌诀 比较级并不难， 先看句中有无than; than前比较级， 无than具体看； 如若句中as.. as现， 务必原级中间站。",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.7144228461723062,
      0.5411620795107034,
      0.9162467002639789,
      0.6992048929663609
    ],
    "page": "jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444",
    "order": 13
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444_8",
    "text": "3.形容词同级比较句式",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.08543316534677226,
      0.576065239551478,
      0.3333333333333333,
      0.5956371049949032
    ],
    "page": "jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444",
    "order": 14
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444_9",
    "text": "(1)“as+形容词原级+as”表示“和……一样……”。注 意此时不能用形容词比较级。 My pen is as new as your pen. 我的钢笔和你的钢笔一样新。 (2)“notas/so十形容词原级+as”表示“不如·…” O Lily isn't as/so careful in writing as Lucy. 在书写方面莉莉没有露西认真。 点拨：可用语法判断法解答 本题。句意： 世界上最 高的山是什么？ 珠穆朗 玛峰！它世界上的其他任 何一座山都高。这是用比较 级来表达最高级的固定句 式。故选A。 ③(桂林中考） Guilin isn't as as Beijing.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.08255339572834174,
      0.5998776758409786,
      0.6570674346052315,
      0.7686850152905199
    ],
    "page": "jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_2444",
    "order": 15
  },
